      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IT'S SOYSAGES (3) flew the lids with a strong early split and led throughout to score an impressive win by 2.75 lengths over 400m at Geelong (22.98). Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. MAURITIAN LUCAS (2) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Ocean Burn (22.52) in a Grade 5. Turned chasing the leaders but kept coming. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Leading chance. MORAINE ARNIE (4) comes off an average performance last start when seventh at Warrnambool over 390m behind Lektra Bills (22.85) in a Grade 5. A big run wouldn't surprise. PAW KIPLIN (1) has been a model of consistency and deserves plenty of thought.",
